Fine-Tuning a Domain-Specific Model for DBT Citizen Bot 

1. Objective 

Purpose 

The current DBT Citizen Bot uses a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture along with multiple prompt-based model calls and business rules to perform query understanding tasks such as: 

Intent Classification 

Scope Detection 

Filter Extraction 

Marathi Query Understanding 

Response Generation 

As the number of schemes, filters, and supported query patterns increases, maintaining multiple prompts and business rules becomes increasingly complex. 

The objective of this initiative is to build a DBT domain-specific Small Language Model (SLM) using fine-tuning, while continuing to leverage the existing RAG system for scheme retrieval and answer generation. 

Fine-Tuning Scope 

The model will be trained to perform: 

Intent Classification 

Filter Extraction 

Scope Detection 

Marathi Query Understanding 

Formatted Answer Generation 

Out of Scope 

The model will not be trained to memorize: 

Scheme Details 

Eligibility Criteria 

Benefits 

Required Documents 

Application Procedures 

Scheme Lists 

These details are dynamic and will continue to be retrieved through the existing RAG pipeline. 

 

