3. Technology Stack 

Technology 

Purpose 

Python 3.10+ 

Primary programming language used for dataset preparation, model training, evaluation, and integration. 

CUDA Toolkit 

NVIDIA GPU acceleration framework required for efficient model training and inference on the L40 GPU. 

PyTorch 

Deep learning framework used to load, train, fine-tune, and evaluate the Qwen model. 

HuggingFace Transformers 

Library used for loading pre-trained Qwen models, tokenization, training, and inference workflows. 

PEFT (Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning) 

Provides LoRA and QLoRA implementations, allowing efficient fine-tuning by training only small adapter layers instead of the full model. 

BitsAndBytes 

Enables 4-bit quantization (QLoRA), significantly reducing GPU memory requirements while maintaining model performance. 

TRL (Transformer Reinforcement Learning) 

Provides supervised fine-tuning (SFT) utilities and training pipelines for instruction-tuning language models. 

vLLM 

High-performance inference engine used to serve the fine-tuned model efficiently in production with lower latency and higher throughput. 

Qdrant 

Vector database used by the RAG pipeline to store embeddings and retrieve relevant scheme information based on user queries. 

LangGraph 

Workflow orchestration framework used to manage the Citizen Bot pipeline, including routing, retrieval, filtering, and response generation. 

 

4. Model Selection 

Move this entire section separately: 

Recommended Base Model 

Qwen3-14B 

Selection Rationale 

Strong instruction-following capability suitable for DBT-specific tasks.  

Reliable structured output generation.  

Supports multilingual interactions including Marathi.  

Good balance between model capability and infrastructure cost.  

Efficient QLoRA fine-tuning on NVIDIA L40 (48 GB VRAM).  

Faster experimentation and retraining cycles.  

Integrates easily with the existing Citizen Bot architecture.  

Suitable for task-oriented fine-tuning rather than knowledge memorization.  

Scalable for future DBT use cases and language support.  

Continues leveraging the existing RAG-based retrieval architecture. 

 

