Phase 5 – Fine-Tuning 

Fine-Tuning Method 

QLoRA (Quantized Low Rank Adaptation) 

Approach 

The base Qwen3-14B model will remain frozen. 

LoRA adapters will be attached to key transformer layers and only these adapter parameters will be trained. 

This significantly reduces: 

GPU Requirements 

Training Cost 

Training Time 

while maintaining performance close to full fine-tuning. 

Configuration 

Base Model: 

Qwen3-14B-Instruct 

Quantization: 

4-bit NF4 

LoRA Rank: 

64 

LoRA Alpha: 

128 

Dropout: 

0.05 

Learning Rate: 

1e-4 to 2e-4 

Epochs: 

2–3 

Sequence Length: 

2048–4096 

Deliverables 

Fine-Tuned LoRA Adapter 

Training Logs 

Checkpoints 

Training Metrics 

 

