7. Conclusion 

The proposed approach is to build a DBT-specific task model using Qwen3-14B and QLoRA fine-tuning while preserving the existing RAG architecture for scheme retrieval. 

The fine-tuned model will specialize in: 

Intent Classification 

Filter Extraction 

Scope Detection 

Marathi Understanding 

Response Formatting 

while the RAG system continues to provide dynamic scheme information. 

This approach minimizes infrastructure changes, leverages existing DBT datasets, improves multilingual capabilities, reduces prompt-engineering complexity, and provides a scalable foundation for future Citizen Bot enhancements. 

 
